
/*
* Thanks to the previous question and the reverse DNS find the name of your host
*/

- Full line answer: host $(ipconfig getpacket en0 | grep yiaddr | awk '{printf $3}')
  6.4.13.10.in-addr.arpa domain name pointer c3r4p6.hive.fi.

- Only host name: host $(ipconfig getpacket en0 | grep yiaddr | awk '{printf $3}') | awk '{printf $NF}'
  c3r4p6.hive.fi.